{"id":24650,"title":"Occult constrictive pericarditis.","abstract":"Four cases of occult pericardial constriction are presented. This condition is not uncommon, but needs high index of suspicion. Integration of detailed echocardiographic evaluation in a given patient with diseases known to cause pericardial involvement can clinch the diagnosis.","date":"2014-10-20","categories":"Cardiovascular Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25327079","annotations":[{"name":"Pericarditis","weight":0.108635,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pericarditis"},{"name":"Pericardium","weight":0.104215,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pericardium"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.0391252,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.0377168,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Occult","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Occult"},{"name":"Constrictive pericarditis","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constrictive_pericarditis"},{"name":"Echocardiography","weight":0.026009,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Echocardiography"},{"name":"Evaluation","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evaluation"},{"name":"Index (publishing)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Index_(publishing)"},{"name":"Vasoconstriction","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vasoconstriction"}]}
